metadata.dc:description: Nasal angiomyolipoma is a anatomoclinical disease that have been described a previous time. It's non epithelial tumour with vascular, muscular and lipomatous elements. It have higher incidence in renal tissue associated with tuberous sclerosis, that hasn't been demonstrated in this case.
metadata.dc:title: Angiomiolipoma nasal.
[Nasal angiomyolipoma].
